MTHULISI Mthethwa&rsquo;s family go to Salmon Bay beach, Ballito every morning, hoping that lifeguards or police divers have found his body.The 21-year-old from J section, KwaMashu, was swept away by strong currents last Tuesday while he was swimming with friends.His aunt, Nokuthula Mtambo (37), told Daily Sun: &ldquo;Authorities told us that when a person drowns, they are normally found within 10 days of the drowning. &ldquo;We are praying that he is found soon. We want to bury him in a dignified manner.&rdquo;KwaDukuza acting lifeguard supervisor Linda Hlophe confirmed that the search for Mthulisi&rsquo;s body was continuing.&ldquo;We are still searching for his body. The area where he was swimming was not designated for swimming. &ldquo;Our lifeguards always escort swimmers away from that area and there are boards in place telling people not to swim there.&rdquo; KZN police spokeswoman Captain Nqobile Gwala said: &ldquo;Police divers and lifeguards are still searching for the victim&rsquo;s body.&rdquo;